# Documentation & ADRs

Docs are part of the deliverable; keep them truthful and in sync with the code.

## Conventions
- Canonical specs live in `docs/` (`requirement.md`, `intermediate-solution.md`,
  `final-solution.md`); treat them as source-of-truth context, not throwaway notes.
- `docs/data-model.md` **mirrors** `db/migrations/` — update it in the **same change** as any
  migration.
- Each deployable/package keeps four docs: `README.md`, `PLAN.md`, `TODO.md`, `AGENTS.md`.
  Update the relevant ones in the same change as code.
- **One decision = one ADR** in `docs/adr/` (Status · Context · Decision · Consequences ·
  Alternatives · Escape hatch). Add the ADR to `docs/adr/README.md`; ADRs are immutable once
  Accepted — supersede with a new one rather than rewriting.
- Write any **new architectural decision** as an ADR before/with the code that implements it.
- Prefer updating an existing doc over creating a new file; never let docs claim something the
  code doesn't do.
